Cattle / 14 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The animals presented the following clinical signs: fever, dullness, discharge, salivation, congestion of the ocular and oral mucosa. There seems to be a co-infection with the bluetongue virus serotype 4.

